I look like hell.

46:00.724 --> 46:02.954
Not at all.
It's just the opposite.

46:03.026 --> 46:05.153
I see where Eloise
gets her looks.

46:07.364 --> 46:08.729
Let's show him
your pictures.

46:08.799 --> 46:09.823
You know,
no, I don't think so...

46:09.900 --> 46:10.889
I'd love to.

46:10.968 --> 46:12.492
No, really.

46:14.071 --> 46:16.938
You know... Okay,
I'm gonna get the keys.

46:17.007 --> 46:19.373
My word, you have
Pocahontas here.

46:19.443 --> 46:22.469
Eloise was state
archery champion
two years in a row.

46:22.546 --> 46:24.036
No.
Oh, Mother.

46:24.114 --> 46:26.981
Don't be modest.
This is Burke Ryan.

46:28.919 --> 46:31.251
I loved you
on The Today Show.

46:32.289 --> 46:33.756
Now how old is she here?

46:33.824 --> 46:35.849
Okay. I got those keys,
so thank you for that.

46:35.926 --> 46:37.860
We gotta go.
Look how cute
you are here.

46:37.928 --> 46:39.953
A-Okay.
A-Okay.

46:40.297 --> 46:41.924
It was very nice
meeting you.
Nice to meet you.

46:41.999 --> 46:44.524
Hope to see you again.
Yeah. Take care. Bye-bye.

46:45.903 --> 46:47.996
I am so glad
you're not dating
that musician.

46:48.071 --> 46:49.436
Mother. Oh, God.

46:54.344 --> 46:56.437
I love you.
Thanks. Thank Bob.

46:58.182 --> 47:00.275
Burke Ryan.
Oh, my God!

47:01.585 --> 47:03.109
Wow.
She's so sweet.

47:03.187 --> 47:04.484
She loves you.

47:04.555 --> 47:05.715
I really enjoyed that.

47:05.789 --> 47:07.347
It was very sweet.

47:09.393 --> 47:13.022
Oh, Mom. No, no, no.
This way. Come on.

47:14.064 --> 47:15.691
Where are we going?

47:16.633 --> 47:18.123
It's fun not knowing,
isn't it?

47:18.202 --> 47:19.191
Ah.

47:19.303 --> 47:20.998
You’ll see.

47:23.407 --> 47:25.671
What, are you trying
to avoid the FBI?

47:25.742 --> 47:28.836
You’ll see. Please,
just get in the truck.

47:35.986 --> 47:37.317
I think I forgot
my hard hat.

47:37.387 --> 47:39.787
Oh, really?
Well, here you go.

47:59.509 --> 48:01.204
What you doing?

48:01.812 --> 48:04.144
Your chariot awaits.

48:05.616 --> 48:07.982
Seriously?
Me, in bucket?

48:08.685 --> 48:10.619
Yes. Trust me.

48:14.892 --> 48:17.656
Have you had any
cold medicine today?

48:17.728 --> 48:19.286
Not today.

48:19.363 --> 48:20.853
We're good.
Okay, now watch this.

48:20.931 --> 48:22.523
Very dangerous.
Fingers.
Uh-huh.

48:22.599 --> 48:24.931
Lock us in. Got it?

48:25.002 --> 48:26.196
Do you know
what you're doing?
Uh-huh.

48:26.270 --> 48:27.362
Ready?
Oh, Lord.

48:27.437 --> 48:28.665
Are we in? Buckled?

48:28.739 --> 48:30.229
Locked? Loaded?
Okay.

48:31.942 --> 48:35.639
All right, here lies
Burke Ryan, dead...

48:36.580 --> 48:40.573
Oh, stop it.
I had a crash course
this morning from Bob.

48:40.651 --> 48:43.085
Who is Bob, and why is
my life in his hands?

48:43.153 --> 48:45.280
Bob's my mom's neighbor.

48:45.355 --> 48:47.550
Current boyfriend
of the moment.

48:47.624 --> 48:49.114
Mmm-hmm.

48:49.760 --> 48:51.625
Okay. Here's
what I was thinking.

48:51.762 --> 48:53.662
I wanted to pick up
from last night.

48:54.865 --> 48:57.356
And I wanted to
get you tickets
to Rogue Wave,

48:57.434 --> 49:00.062
but they've been
sold out for weeks.

49:01.204 --> 49:05.698
So, I figured
where there is a will,
there is a way.

49:21.525 --> 49:24.119
Heaven is a switchboard
that you want to fight

49:24.194 --> 49:26.458
She would even miss you
if you taught her sight

49:26.530 --> 49:28.794
Power politician
leaning to the right

49:28.865 --> 49:32.733
Baby's got a trust fund
that she'll want to go off
like that

49:32.803 --> 49:35.203
Get off my stack

49:35.272 --> 49:37.035
leave a little window

49:37.107 --> 49:40.042
Get off of my stack

49:47.851 --> 49:49.751
Now we wear
same-colored yellow uniforms

49:49.820 --> 49:51.082
Sky is burning
but at least we're warm

50:00.497 --> 50:02.590
If I had a nickel
for every time
I saw a concert

50:02.666 --> 50:04.998
from a telephone truck,
I'd be...

50:05.969 --> 50:08.199
Thank you.
It was exquisite.

50:08.271 --> 50:10.102
Don't thank me.
Thank Bob.

50:10.173 --> 50:11.606
Thank you, Bob.

50:12.442 --> 50:14.342
Hey, I got your book.

50:14.411 --> 50:15.400
I'm halfway through it.

50:15.479 --> 50:16.605
Really?

50:17.247 --> 50:19.909
Well, wait till you get
to the recipe chapters.

50:19.983 --> 50:21.780
They're top-notch.

50:25.455 --> 50:27.548
I'm sorry
about your wife.

50:29.192 --> 50:31.854
How come you didn't tell me
that's what happened?

50:34.164 --> 50:36.428
I don't know.
Never came up.

50:39.102 --> 50:41.593
Well, it sounded like
you really loved her.

50:43.340 --> 50:44.830
Yeah, I did.

50:46.710 --> 50:48.268
But that was
a long time ago.

50:49.646 --> 50:51.136
Three years?

50:51.848 --> 50:53.645
Twenty-one in dog years.

50:58.221 --> 51:01.952
I had a really,
really great time.

51:02.859 --> 51:05.054
Me, too.
That was really fun.

51:19.176 --> 51:20.473
What?

51:20.877 --> 51:24.779
I'm waiting
to watch you strut back
to your bitchin' rig.

51:28.785 --> 51:30.116
All right.

51:31.555 --> 51:32.544
Bye.

52:10.001 --> 52:12.993
Is that the international
song for "got laid"?

52:13.605 --> 52:15.095
No! Hardly.

52:15.507 --> 52:18.806
Come on, throw me a bone.
What happened last night?

52:19.277 --> 52:20.767
It was fun.

52:21.580 --> 52:23.605
So, are you going
to see him again?

52:23.682 --> 52:26.276
I don't know. Maybe.

52:29.121 --> 52:33.353
May I just point out
that you broke up
with Tyler 72 hours ago

52:33.425 --> 52:35.154
and now you're dating
some other guy

52:35.227 --> 52:37.457
who's not even gonna be
in town for 72 hours?

52:37.529 --> 52:38.757
Can I just point that out?

52:38.830 --> 52:40.991
Okay, we're...
We're not dating.

52:41.399 --> 52:46.530
We just met and,
you know, I like him.

52:48.073 --> 52:49.973
We're just hanging out.

52:51.009 --> 52:52.943
Well, just be careful.

52:53.678 --> 52:56.442
Men are hairy.

52:57.582 --> 52:59.413
Thank you for that.

54:47.993 --> 54:50.461
Two minutes.
Give him two minutes.

54:51.596 --> 54:53.791
He gets called away
for emergencies, you know.

55:01.072 --> 55:04.371
"Her freckles frame eyes
the color of mermaid's tears

55:04.442 --> 55:08.310
"Her ears like waking up
to the sound of
children at play"

55:08.380 --> 55:11.645
"My first five senses are
reeling like an old-school
cassette tape

55:11.716 --> 55:15.208
"rewound and played
electric relaxation all day"

55:15.287 --> 55:19.121
"You and your phallus
may run this world

55:19.190 --> 55:23.957
"But this Amazon bitch
will cut you down to size!"

55:26.631 --> 55:28.064
Thank you.

55:35.540 --> 55:37.303
That was slamming.

55:37.676 --> 55:40.201
Thank you.
I tried to mix up
the iambic pentameter

55:40.278 --> 55:42.542
with a little
haiku motif.

55:42.614 --> 55:45.048
Kick-ass, Mart. Drink?

55:45.116 --> 55:46.583
Yeah, all around, on me.

55:46.651 --> 55:50.747
And can we have more
of the Istanbul Black
Demon shisha, please?

55:50.822 --> 55:51.880
Black Demon?

55:51.956 --> 55:54.447
Thank you. So wicked.
Want to try it?

55:54.526 --> 55:55.686
-Go ahead, try it.
-Okay.

55:55.760 --> 55:57.022
"Try me."

55:59.097 --> 56:00.291
Sure.

56:13.878 --> 56:17.006
Shit. Excuse me
for one second,
will you?

56:17.215 --> 56:18.944
Who is that man?

56:25.457 --> 56:28.119
I beg you, please
make sense of this.

56:28.360 --> 56:30.328
I'm just enjoying
a little local flavor.

56:30.395 --> 56:32.863
Since when do you
enjoy anything?

56:32.931 --> 56:34.398
How did you even find me?

56:34.466 --> 56:36.957
I'm Lane goddamn Marshall,
okay?

56:38.203 --> 56:39.670
You asked directions
from your concierge.

56:39.738 --> 56:40.830
What is going on here?

56:40.905 --> 56:43.373
We're on the verge
of the deal
of the century here

56:43.441 --> 56:45.033
and you're off playing
Prince of Persia.

56:45.110 --> 56:46.941
Drinks, gentlemen?
No. Get out of here.

56:47.011 --> 56:48.569
Hey, Lane.

56:48.646 --> 56:51.046
No, thank you.
Will you calm down?

56:51.116 --> 56:52.947
I will not calm down.

56:53.017 --> 56:55.611
Their CEO is coming
in two days.

56:57.222 --> 56:59.713
Do you have any idea
the blood, sweat and tears

56:59.791 --> 57:02.225
it's taken me to put
this thing together?

57:02.293 --> 57:04.989
You know, Unicom didn't
even know your name
six months ago.

57:05.063 --> 57:06.325
I know and I appreciate it.

57:06.831 --> 57:07.820
No, you don't.
Yes, I do.

57:07.899 --> 57:10.026
No, you don't!
Lane.

57:10.101 --> 57:11.762
Friend to friend,

57:13.605 --> 57:15.505
do you not want this?

57:20.979 --> 57:22.378
You can tell me.

57:26.518 --> 57:29.715
Look, I'm ready.

57:30.321 --> 57:31.413
Okay?

57:31.489 --> 57:32.513
So, for the next two days,
you're gonna be

57:32.590 --> 57:34.820
where I tell you to be
when I tell you to be there?

57:36.060 --> 57:37.789
Yes. Scout's honor.

57:38.897 --> 57:40.762
You with the scouting.

57:41.666 --> 57:42.997
Oh, God.

57:44.035 --> 57:45.434
Will you relax?
You're gonna have
a heart attack.

57:45.503 --> 57:48.472
I had a heart attack.
I had four heart attacks
on the way here.

57:51.709 --> 57:54.803
So, who are these
fine folks that you're
consorting with?

57:55.814 --> 57:59.113
Just people I've met.

58:00.885 --> 58:01.977
Yeah?

58:05.290 --> 58:06.951
Her name's Eloise.

58:07.258 --> 58:10.318
Well, what hath
struck the earth?
Details.

58:12.497 --> 58:13.828
She's...

58:16.067 --> 58:17.227
Yeah?

58:21.206 --> 58:22.969
That's great.
Yeah.

58:23.041 --> 58:24.065
That's great.

58:24.142 --> 58:25.268
So, I'm gonna get back.

58:25.343 --> 58:26.810
Yeah, we'd better.

58:32.350 --> 58:36.684
All right, yo,
a pleasure to meet you guys.
Welcome to the rainy city.

58:38.423 --> 58:40.482
Should I belly dance?

59:58.570 --> 01:00:02.506
It's tragic.
They were so young.

01:00:02.574 --> 01:00:03.905
It's just so sad.

01:00:03.975 --> 01:00:04.999
I know.

01:00:05.476 --> 01:00:08.536
I don't know how you
deal with all that
death every day.

01:00:08.613 --> 01:00:11.047
Well, I have to deal
with it no matter what.

01:00:12.350 --> 01:00:16.582
I think that
funerals are archaic
and a waste of money.

01:00:17.221 --> 01:00:22.386
Actually, funerals
are an important ritual
in the grieving process.

01:00:23.394 --> 01:00:26.761
They don't just recognize
that a life has ended.

01:00:26.831 --> 01:00:29.698
They recognize
that a life was lived.

01:00:30.735 --> 01:00:32.600
My wife's funeral...

01:00:33.237 --> 01:00:34.761
Burke, you don't
have to.

01:00:34.839 --> 01:00:35.863
No, it's okay.
That's okay.

01:00:35.940 --> 01:00:40.604
Which was actually
here in Seattle,
was a celebration.

01:00:41.112 --> 01:00:43.080
It was a beautiful day
in March,

01:00:43.147 --> 01:00:44.739
St. Patrick's Day, actually.

01:00:44.816 --> 01:00:46.875
And her family
has a little plot,

01:00:46.951 --> 01:00:48.919
so we set up
chairs and candles.

01:00:48.987 --> 01:00:53.083
And it had been raining
for two weeks straight.
Pouring.

01:00:53.157 --> 01:00:55.318
But on that day,
the sun came out.

01:00:55.393 --> 01:00:57.088
The dahlias were
blooming in the ground

01:00:57.161 --> 01:00:58.753
as if they were
welcoming her.

01:00:58.830 --> 01:01:01.697
It was... It was magic.

01:01:05.169 --> 01:01:07.603
That was a healing
for my family.

01:01:15.613 --> 01:01:16.944
Dahlias?

01:01:19.417 --> 01:01:20.748
Dahlias.

01:01:21.586 --> 01:01:24.282
Dahlias. That was
her favorite flower.

01:01:27.091 --> 01:01:29.821
Dahlias don't bloom
here until the fall.

01:01:31.996 --> 01:01:34.624
Well, maybe they were
early that year.

01:01:35.333 --> 01:01:36.698
It's getting late.

01:01:36.768 --> 01:01:38.668
We should hit
the road, Burke.

01:01:53.418 --> 01:01:54.612
He didn't go, did he?

01:02:04.762 --> 01:02:05.990
No.

01:03:04.388 --> 01:03:05.377
Oh.

01:03:06.190 --> 01:03:07.987
So beautiful here.

01:03:09.694 --> 01:03:12.561
Look. Look, you can
see my parents' house.

01:03:13.264 --> 01:03:15.323
Right... Yeah, right there.

01:03:17.135 --> 01:03:18.762
Okay, your turn.

01:03:19.036 --> 01:03:22.130
Big smile. Time for
that tourist snapshot.

01:03:22.907 --> 01:03:25.205
It's gonna go
right on the wall
in the living room.

01:03:28.346 --> 01:03:30.712
You're not smiling.
Would you smile, please?

01:03:31.749 --> 01:03:35.378
Okay, three, two, one.

01:03:36.053 --> 01:03:37.486
Say "cheese."

01:04:37.248 --> 01:04:40.183
Recovery starts with
acceptance, Olivia.

01:04:40.251 --> 01:04:43.220
I think you're
well on your way.
Okay. Good.

01:04:43.421 --> 01:04:45.252
Who's next? Anybody?

01:04:46.290 --> 01:04:48.622
Come on, people,
this is what these
smaller sessions are for.

01:04:48.693 --> 01:04:50.718
Let's get our hands up.
Come on, participate.

01:04:54.031 --> 01:04:55.658
Martha, please.

01:04:57.368 --> 01:04:58.392
I don't know. I...

01:04:58.469 --> 01:05:00.596
No, Martha, "I don't know"
never got anybody anywhere.

01:05:00.671 --> 01:05:03.162
So, please,
this is your assessment.

01:05:04.108 --> 01:05:06.508
Let's make
the most of it, okay?

01:05:07.945 --> 01:05:10.345
I think
I'm coming to terms
with some of my anger.

01:05:10.414 --> 01:05:11.938
Good.
And I'm gonna try

01:05:12.016 --> 01:05:13.608
to stop projecting it
onto others.

01:05:13.684 --> 01:05:15.948
Fine. Work on that
in group this afternoon.

01:05:16.020 --> 01:05:18.853
All right?
All right, next. Anybody.

01:05:21.559 --> 01:05:24.187
Come on, people.
Walter, how about you?

01:05:26.831 --> 01:05:28.890
I feel I'm getting
a lot out of the seminar.

01:05:28.966 --> 01:05:30.729
Like what?

01:05:31.402 --> 01:05:33.962
Come on, there's
no right answer here.
Open up.

01:05:34.972 --> 01:05:36.234
Well...

01:05:37.742 --> 01:05:39.266
It's just...

01:05:41.345 --> 01:05:43.905
It still hurts.

01:05:43.981 --> 01:05:46.916
Okay, that's a given, Walter.
What are you doing about it?

01:05:48.185 --> 01:05:49.243
I'm trying.

01:05:49.320 --> 01:05:52.881
No, Walter. I don't think that
you're trying hard enough.

01:05:52.957 --> 01:05:54.549
I don't know
how to try any harder.

01:05:54.625 --> 01:05:56.320
You don't know how?

01:05:56.560 --> 01:05:58.926
You don't know how?
Have I not been up here
the last three days?

01:05:58.996 --> 01:06:00.224
Have you not been
listening to me?

01:06:00.298 --> 01:06:01.822
I mean, you don't know
how, Walter?

01:06:01.899 --> 01:06:03.298
No, I...
Then spit it out!

01:06:03.367 --> 01:06:05.028
Come on, what is it?
What is it?

01:06:05.102 --> 01:06:06.364
You want to know what?

01:06:06.437 --> 01:06:08.530
He should be pitching
Little League right now.

01:06:09.407 --> 01:06:11.967
If he'd stayed in the car,
he'd be playing video games,

01:06:12.043 --> 01:06:13.943
he'd be spray-painting
his skateboard,

01:06:14.011 --> 01:06:15.842
he'd be pissing me off
by being a kid,

01:06:15.913 --> 01:06:17.278
but he's never
gonna do any of that

01:06:17.348 --> 01:06:19.407
because he's
in a goddamn box!

01:06:57.521 --> 01:06:58.852
Walter.

01:07:02.893 --> 01:07:04.520
You're stuck.

01:07:06.163 --> 01:07:07.562
You can't move
forward because

01:07:07.631 --> 01:07:09.792
you've got your eyes
on the rearview mirror.

01:07:12.069 --> 01:07:16.005
The death of your son has
become the death of you,

01:07:17.041 --> 01:07:20.977
your marriage,
your job. Everything.

01:07:23.547 --> 01:07:25.037
It's just...

01:07:28.652 --> 01:07:30.984
I don't know
how to get it back.

01:07:34.592 --> 01:07:36.219
You're a contractor, right?

01:07:39.363 --> 01:07:40.421
Build it.

01:07:41.332 --> 01:07:43.095
One brick at a time.

01:07:47.972 --> 01:07:49.303
Watch your step.
Little field trip today.

01:07:50.007 --> 01:07:51.531
Thank you.
Hi. How you doing, Brenda?

01:07:51.609 --> 01:07:53.873
Good. Trust me.

01:08:07.725 --> 01:08:09.625
All right, follow me.

01:08:13.264 --> 01:08:15.994
Wait right around
the corner, Lorraine.
Thanks.

01:08:17.568 --> 01:08:18.626
Now, watch your step.

01:08:18.702 --> 01:08:21.000
I'll see you
out there, okay?

01:08:22.540 --> 01:08:25.907
Okay.
You all right there? Okay.

01:08:25.975 --> 01:08:26.965
Thanks.

01:08:28.045 --> 01:08:29.205
I'm not going out there.

01:08:31.582 --> 01:08:33.607
I can't go out there.

01:08:36.187 --> 01:08:40.419
Walter. You're not a janitor.

01:08:41.158 --> 01:08:42.318
You're a contractor.

01:08:50.201 --> 01:08:51.634
After you.

01:09:05.483 --> 01:09:07.747
Now let's fill
this thing up.

01:09:12.022 --> 01:09:14.183
All right, gang, let’s go.

01:11:30.761 --> 01:11:32.854
He'd have gotten
a kick out of this.

01:11:39.670 --> 01:11:45.199
Thank you
for reminding me.

01:11:46.810 --> 01:11:49.108
You reminded
yourself, Walter.

01:11:52.116 --> 01:11:53.947
I couldn't hold him.

01:11:55.552 --> 01:11:57.884
At the end,
I couldn't hold him.

01:11:59.390 --> 01:12:03.292
The paramedics said
not to move him, so...

01:12:07.398 --> 01:12:09.423
I want you to have this.

01:12:15.039 --> 01:12:17.007
Beautiful boy, Walter.

01:12:22.446 --> 01:12:24.607
If you ever need
a remodel.

01:12:53.610 --> 01:12:55.510
I'll be right there.

01:12:59.416 --> 01:13:02.783
I didn't go to her funeral.
And I...

01:13:03.620 --> 01:13:07.386
Look, I haven't spoken
to her parents since I...

01:13:08.092 --> 01:13:09.457
Yeah, I didn't
take care of Rocky.

01:13:09.526 --> 01:13:10.857
I stopped talking
to her friends.

01:13:10.928 --> 01:13:14.364
I threw out everything
that even smelled of her. I...

01:13:17.167 --> 01:13:20.796
Listen, I wasn't judging you
or trying to trip you up.

01:13:23.841 --> 01:13:25.706
Can I say something?

01:13:26.610 --> 01:13:30.512
And this comes
from a place of
total humility.

01:13:31.315 --> 01:13:32.942
With the acknowledgment
that my life

01:13:33.016 --> 01:13:38.818
is a day-by-day experiment
in really bad decisions.

01:13:40.991 --> 01:13:42.185
But...

01:13:43.827 --> 01:13:45.795
You're really messed up.

01:13:47.698 --> 01:13:49.427
I mean, maybe
you need someone

01:13:49.500 --> 01:13:53.027
to nudge you
to do these things that
you don't want to do,

01:13:53.103 --> 01:13:57.972
like talk to her parents
or take care of Rocky,

01:13:58.675 --> 01:14:00.336
whatever Rocky is.

01:14:01.145 --> 01:14:02.544
What is Rocky?

01:14:02.613 --> 01:14:03.773
It's a parrot.

01:14:03.847 --> 01:14:04.905
Parrot?

01:14:04.982 --> 01:14:06.415
Her parrot.

01:14:06.884 --> 01:14:08.784
He's loud and he shits
all over the place.

01:14:10.587 --> 01:14:11.986
It's a parrot.

01:14:14.491 --> 01:14:15.480
She made me promise

01:14:15.559 --> 01:14:19.393
that if anything ever
happened to her that I'd...

01:14:21.665 --> 01:14:23.599
I mean, it sounds...
It's crazy.
What?

01:14:23.667 --> 01:14:27.364
That I would release him
into the wild.

01:14:28.605 --> 01:14:30.334
And you haven't
done that, have you?

01:14:31.141 --> 01:14:34.736
No. No,
her parents took him.

01:14:37.881 --> 01:14:39.712
Didn't you say
her parents live here?

01:14:41.452 --> 01:14:42.441
Mmm-hmm.

01:14:42.986 --> 01:14:44.578
Two birds, one stone.

01:14:44.655 --> 01:14:46.452
Come on.
Eloise, no.

01:14:46.523 --> 01:14:48.548
Why?
Because it's her...

01:14:48.892 --> 01:14:50.359
Her father...

01:14:50.427 --> 01:14:52.327
Hmm...
No, you know...

01:14:52.663 --> 01:14:54.324
It's just... It's more
complicated than that.

01:14:54.398 --> 01:14:56.696
I'm sure it's... I'm sure
it's very complicated.

01:14:56.767 --> 01:14:58.928
Eloise, no.

01:15:10.614 --> 01:15:12.138
So, that's it.

01:15:12.349 --> 01:15:13.907
That's it.

01:15:14.985 --> 01:15:15.974
Do you want me to...

01:15:16.053 --> 01:15:19.045
Do you want me
to go with you or... No.

01:15:19.223 --> 01:15:22.056
I don't think that would
go over so well.

01:15:24.661 --> 01:15:27.357
Look, you know what?
I don't even know
if they're home.

01:15:27.431 --> 01:15:29.399
They probably didn't
even keep the bird.

01:15:30.267 --> 01:15:31.495
Burke.

01:15:41.111 --> 01:15:42.840
Did I mention
that her father
is an ex-Marine?

01:15:42.913 --> 01:15:44.642
Ex-Marine. Yeah.

01:16:25.322 --> 01:16:27.722
All right, now.
So, you add in some of these
mega-mergers

01:16:27.791 --> 01:16:29.918
that we're talking about.
BHP...

01:16:51.348 --> 01:16:53.248
That's right.
Guess who.

01:16:53.317 --> 01:16:56.480
You never thought
you'd see me again,
did you?

01:17:06.597 --> 01:17:10.033
Another damn commercial.
How about some
fresh tea, hon?

01:17:10.100 --> 01:17:11.533
Oh, thanks.

01:17:20.410 --> 01:17:22.844
What the hell's
going on with you?

01:17:23.714 --> 01:17:25.511
Huh? What are you
up to now?

01:17:25.582 --> 01:17:26.708
What, honey?

01:17:26.783 --> 01:17:28.011
I'm talking to Rocky.

01:17:29.119 --> 01:17:30.143
Honey,
don't tease him.

01:17:30.220 --> 01:17:31.812
You know it gets him...
I'm not teasing him.

01:17:31.888 --> 01:17:34.550
He was doing the damn
car alarm again.

01:17:36.059 --> 01:17:37.993
Honey, could you
get me some
lemon, please?

01:17:38.061 --> 01:17:39.119
What?

01:17:39.196 --> 01:17:40.629
Could you get
some lemon, please?

01:17:40.697 --> 01:17:41.755
Yes, it's right here.

01:17:41.832 --> 01:17:43.094
Shut up!

01:17:44.034 --> 01:17:46.559
Just don't cut yourself
when you're slicing it.

01:17:46.637 --> 01:17:48.969
I won't cut myself.
Don't worry.

01:18:02.786 --> 01:18:04.617
Go! Go! Go!

01:18:05.622 --> 01:18:06.748
Start it up, go!

01:18:06.823 --> 01:18:07.915
What's going on?

01:18:07.991 --> 01:18:09.356
Go. Just drive.

01:18:09.426 --> 01:18:10.518
What?

01:18:10.594 --> 01:18:11.754
Go. Just drive.

01:18:11.828 --> 01:18:12.817
I'm going. I'm going.
Just drive!

01:18:12.896 --> 01:18:14.921
Come on, let’s get
out of here. Go, go!

01:18:14.998 --> 01:18:16.693
Go, go, go, go!

01:18:18.368 --> 01:18:20.268
Jesus, what happened?

01:18:20.337 --> 01:18:22.567
I got the bird.
That's all that matters.

01:18:22.639 --> 01:18:25.130
Oh, God. Were they...
Were they that upset?

01:18:25.208 --> 01:18:26.436
They will be.

01:18:26.510 --> 01:18:27.602
What?

01:18:31.848 --> 01:18:34.476
What happened to
"two birds, one stone"?

01:18:34.551 --> 01:18:35.916
One bird's all
I could manage.

01:18:35.986 --> 01:18:38.454
Eloise, they never would've
given me that bird.

01:18:38.522 --> 01:18:40.285
Trust me.
You don't know that.

01:18:40.357 --> 01:18:41.881
I cut my losses.

01:18:41.958 --> 01:18:43.084
If she wanted this
bird turned loose,

01:18:43.160 --> 01:18:44.491
this is the way
to get it done.

01:18:47.664 --> 01:18:49.427
Okay. All right.

01:19:10.620 --> 01:19:13.783
This isn't animal cruelty
or something, is it?

01:19:16.727 --> 01:19:19.025
It wasn't my idea.
It was your idea.

01:19:19.096 --> 01:19:21.792
It wasn't my idea.
It was her idea.

01:19:23.333 --> 01:19:25.597
Well, let’s let him decide.

01:20:09.513 --> 01:20:10.707
Okay.

01:20:14.551 --> 01:20:18.885
This looks like a good place,
so I guess this is goodbye.

01:20:21.758 --> 01:20:22.952
Go on.

01:20:23.760 --> 01:20:25.853
Come on, Rocky.
Fly away.

01:20:26.630 --> 01:20:28.825
Come on, let’s go!
Giddyup!

01:20:30.200 --> 01:20:33.260
You'll see the world.
Come on. Meet some girls.

01:20:38.008 --> 01:20:39.407
No, come on.

01:20:40.043 --> 01:20:41.977
Go on, get out of here.

01:20:42.746 --> 01:20:44.646
No, Rock. Come on. Go.

01:20:45.382 --> 01:20:46.713
Come here.

01:20:50.453 --> 01:20:52.683
Fly away.
Rocky, look at me.

01:20:56.626 --> 01:20:58.890
Giddyup! Giddyup!

01:21:01.164 --> 01:21:03.826
All right,
now you're pissing me off.

01:21:04.501 --> 01:21:06.162
You want to go back
to Semper Fi's house?

01:21:07.904 --> 01:21:09.667
All right, you know what?
You're on your own.

01:22:33.623 --> 01:22:35.022
How'd it go?

01:22:35.625 --> 01:22:37.388
Mission accomplished.

01:22:37.460 --> 01:22:38.984
Was he happy?

01:22:41.698 --> 01:22:43.063
Are you happy?

01:22:46.536 --> 01:22:49.096
It's a bird.
I set it free.

01:22:51.074 --> 01:22:52.063
Oh.

01:23:00.550 --> 01:23:02.450
I need you to take me
back to the hotel.

01:23:03.186 --> 01:23:04.414
Okay.

01:23:07.357 --> 01:23:09.222
I feel better
for having done it, okay?

01:23:09.292 --> 01:23:12.489
Listen, you don't have to
talk about it if you
don't want to. Really.

01:23:12.562 --> 01:23:13.756
Just tell me what to say
and I'll say it.

01:23:13.830 --> 01:23:14.854
No.

01:23:15.231 --> 01:23:16.493
I don't... I don't know.
I'm not good...

01:23:16.566 --> 01:23:18.329
I haven't thought
this through.

01:23:19.636 --> 01:23:22.730
You know, Burke,
I like you. I like you.

01:23:23.606 --> 01:23:24.937
Not the author.

01:23:25.475 --> 01:23:26.806
Not the guy
with the microphone.

01:23:26.876 --> 01:23:28.605
And I just...
I just want to help.

01:23:29.913 --> 01:23:32.438
You know what, Eloise,
I just...

01:23:33.316 --> 01:23:36.615
I need you to take me
back to the hotel, right now,

01:23:37.053 --> 01:23:38.714
and I need you
to respect that.
Burke, I will...

01:23:38.788 --> 01:23:41.916
Damn it!
You just don't know
when to quit, do you?

01:23:41.992 --> 01:23:44.859
I asked you to stop
and you just keep on.

01:23:45.762 --> 01:23:48.356
Maybe you're the one
who needs psychoanalysis.

01:23:48.431 --> 01:23:50.456
Leave me alone,
all right?

01:23:52.836 --> 01:23:55.100
I can catch
my own ride back.

01:24:41.017 --> 01:24:42.780
It's about time.

01:24:43.353 --> 01:24:45.583
Oh, my God!
Where the hell
have you been?

01:24:45.655 --> 01:24:47.316
It's not important.
Uh-huh.

01:24:47.390 --> 01:24:49.017
Well, let me
tell you something
that is important.

01:24:49.092 --> 01:24:51.117
You blew off dinner
and Vernon's here.

01:24:51.194 --> 01:24:52.388
I mean, Jesus,
you have got to...

01:24:52.462 --> 01:24:53.793
Lane!

01:24:57.801 --> 01:25:00.531
I'll meet with him
first thing in the morning,
make sure he feels the love.

01:25:00.603 --> 01:25:02.628
You, meanwhile,
accept their offer,

01:25:02.705 --> 01:25:04.263
but tell them the DVD
rollout is too late.

01:25:04.340 --> 01:25:06.035
I want it bumped up
to next month.

01:25:08.144 --> 01:25:09.441
Jesus.

01:25:10.980 --> 01:25:13.244
What the hell
happened to you, man?

01:25:13.316 --> 01:25:14.874
I can't wait to
get out of this city.

01:25:16.553 --> 01:25:17.747
Hey!

01:25:18.721 --> 01:25:19.881
Is everything cool?

01:25:19.956 --> 01:25:21.514
Absolutely.

01:25:21.591 --> 01:25:23.991
Yeah? Anything of note
happen this afternoon?

01:25:24.060 --> 01:25:25.049
Not particularly.

01:25:25.128 --> 01:25:26.322
What about Eloise?

01:25:26.629 --> 01:25:30.030
Stop! Wait! Listen to me.

01:25:31.101 --> 01:25:34.662
You know, you can
talk to me if you want to.

01:25:36.473 --> 01:25:39.704
I know. I get all mixed up.
I get caught up
in this business shit,

01:25:39.776 --> 01:25:41.641
but I want you to know

01:25:43.279 --> 01:25:45.543
that I'm there for you
if you need me to be.

01:25:48.818 --> 01:25:50.080
She's gone.

01:25:50.253 --> 01:25:51.914
She's gone?
What do you mean,
she's gone?

01:25:54.224 --> 01:25:56.624
I don't know, man, I just...

01:25:56.693 --> 01:25:58.320
I screwed it up.

01:26:00.029 --> 01:26:03.692
I threw all my...
All my bullshit in her face.

01:26:05.902 --> 01:26:07.995
It could've been something.

01:26:09.739 --> 01:26:11.604
Night, Lane.
Burke.

01:26:12.609 --> 01:26:14.338
Sleep well.
Big day tomorrow.

01:26:14.410 --> 01:26:15.434
Burke.

01:26:17.280 --> 01:26:18.611
Burke.

01:26:35.965 --> 01:26:37.125
She'd be
proud of you.

01:26:37.200 --> 01:26:38.224
I didn't go
to her funeral.

01:26:38.301 --> 01:26:39.325
Hypocrite.

01:26:39.402 --> 01:26:40.494
You're stuck.

01:26:40.570 --> 01:26:42.162
You can't move
forward because

01:26:42.238 --> 01:26:43.762
you've got your eyes
on the rearview mirror.

01:26:43.840 --> 01:26:44.966
You're
really messed up.

01:26:45.041 --> 01:26:46.406
Swerved into a pole.

01:26:46.476 --> 01:26:48.205
She died instantly.

01:26:51.681 --> 01:26:54.411
When are you gonna stop
lying, son?

01:27:39.896 --> 01:27:41.989
Good morning, sire.
This way.

01:27:42.065 --> 01:27:43.089
What happened to you?

01:27:43.166 --> 01:27:45.134
Went for a little run.
It's refreshing.

01:27:45.201 --> 01:27:48.967
You know, Vernon went
for the international
and DVD rollout.

01:27:49.038 --> 01:27:52.098
Yeah. Old man
likes what he sees
and we are Rolls-Royce.

01:27:52.175 --> 01:27:53.506
Get it done.
First things first,

01:27:53.576 --> 01:27:56.272
I need you to
shake some hands
with somebody here.

01:27:57.714 --> 01:27:59.204
Mr. Vernon,
it's a pleasure...

01:28:07.991 --> 01:28:09.891
Lane goddamn Marshall.

01:28:15.865 --> 01:28:17.162
Well,

01:28:20.203 --> 01:28:22.068
this is unexpected.

01:28:27.076 --> 01:28:28.509
I'm sorry.

01:28:30.046 --> 01:28:33.675
Lane told me the truth.

01:28:38.755 --> 01:28:42.589
You don't deserve
what you put
yourself through.

01:28:45.795 --> 01:28:47.592
I hope that
you can find a way

01:28:47.664 --> 01:28:50.633
to somehow give
yourself a break

01:28:52.101 --> 01:28:55.832
because if you don't,
this is... This is
gonna be your life.

01:28:58.875 --> 01:29:00.809
I just think that's...

01:29:02.879 --> 01:29:04.676
That's just sad.

01:29:08.418 --> 01:29:10.318
That's it. That's...

01:29:11.454 --> 01:29:13.445
That's all I came to say.

01:29:21.364 --> 01:29:24.492
So, just take care
of yourself, okay?

01:29:44.487 --> 01:29:46.182
How's about it,
folks, huh?

01:29:47.423 --> 01:29:50.256
Has it been a week
of miracles or what?

01:29:54.063 --> 01:29:58.295
How many of you
can't get enough
of Burke Ryan?

01:30:00.336 --> 01:30:03.328
I bet that you
would love to see him

01:30:03.406 --> 01:30:06.637
in your living room
from 3:00 p.m.
to 4:00 p.m. every day

01:30:06.709 --> 01:30:08.472
on your local
syndicated channel.

01:30:08.544 --> 01:30:11.240
Huh? Yes!

01:30:13.383 --> 01:30:15.943
We'll see what we
can do about that.

01:30:16.018 --> 01:30:22.184
Now, without further ado,
the man of the hour,
Burke Ryan.

01:30:40.443 --> 01:30:42.911
Thank you.
Please have a seat.

01:30:44.080 --> 01:30:46.480
Thank you.
Have a seat, please.

01:30:48.718 --> 01:30:50.151
Gosh, I'm...

01:30:51.788 --> 01:30:53.619
I'm feeling okay.
How are you?

01:30:53.689 --> 01:30:55.213
A-Okay!

01:30:59.529 --> 01:31:00.860
Sir, I need to
see your badge.

01:31:00.930 --> 01:31:02.557
I'm sorry, what?
Sir, your badge.

01:31:02.632 --> 01:31:05.624
I got a badge.
He's a damn thief,
you know.

01:31:05.968 --> 01:31:07.492
Son of a bitch
broke into my house
and took something.

01:31:07.570 --> 01:31:08.935
There's your badge.
You can keep it.

01:31:09.005 --> 01:31:10.097
You keep it!

01:31:10.173 --> 01:31:13.574
We have made
a lot of progress
in the last few days,

01:31:14.811 --> 01:31:16.472
but don't forget,

01:31:17.246 --> 01:31:18.975
it's just a foundation
for the future.

01:31:24.020 --> 01:31:25.487
Excuse me.

01:31:34.096 --> 01:31:37.122
You know...
Boy, I'm sorry.

01:31:41.571 --> 01:31:43.300
I... I've...

01:31:48.744 --> 01:31:51.076
I can't lie
to you guys anymore.

01:31:56.018 --> 01:31:57.952
You know, I stand here

01:32:00.323 --> 01:32:03.315
and I watch you all
confront your pain.

01:32:07.396 --> 01:32:08.954
And I envy you

01:32:10.666 --> 01:32:12.065
because

01:32:15.404 --> 01:32:17.497
I haven't confronted mine.

01:32:24.580 --> 01:32:26.912
I didn't want it
to be my fault.

01:32:27.917 --> 01:32:29.782
My wife's accident.

01:32:32.021 --> 01:32:33.648
It was raining.

01:32:35.558 --> 01:32:37.025
This dog

01:32:42.899 --> 01:32:45.129
in the middle of the road.

01:32:47.870 --> 01:32:49.667
We had been arguing

01:32:51.774 --> 01:32:55.301
over paint colors
for the kitchen.

01:32:59.148 --> 01:33:00.638
Paint colors.

01:33:07.189 --> 01:33:09.453
But what I haven't told you

01:33:17.633 --> 01:33:20.193
is that I was
driving the car,

01:33:23.773 --> 01:33:25.001
not her.

01:33:33.149 --> 01:33:34.844
I killed my wife.

01:33:47.330 --> 01:33:49.230
I'm so sorry.

01:33:59.709 --> 01:34:01.973
It was just
an accident, son.

01:34:07.216 --> 01:34:08.877
That's all it was.

01:34:20.496 --> 01:34:22.361
There was nothing
you could have done.

01:34:22.431 --> 01:34:23.420
No.

01:34:23.499 --> 01:34:24.488
No, it's true.

01:34:24.567 --> 01:34:27.536
It was just one of those
freak accidents.

01:34:28.037 --> 01:34:30.801
Listen to me.
We never blamed you.

01:34:32.108 --> 01:34:33.439
Never.

01:34:33.809 --> 01:34:37.108
All we really wanted to do
was mourn with you, son.

01:34:37.179 --> 01:34:40.114
We didn't know what to do.
We couldn't find you.

01:34:40.182 --> 01:34:42.377
That's been the worst part.

01:34:51.494 --> 01:34:53.018
It's okay.

01:36:09.572 --> 01:36:13.133
Hey. Come here.

01:36:17.179 --> 01:36:21.445
I was thinking that maybe
I should've had you do that
a long time ago.

01:36:25.254 --> 01:36:26.516
You gonna be all right?

01:36:26.589 --> 01:36:27.988
Yeah, in time.

01:36:28.124 --> 01:36:30.888
Mr. Ryan? Ted Vernon.

01:36:31.994 --> 01:36:34.519
That was something.

01:36:36.031 --> 01:36:38.022
Yeah, that was
something, huh?

01:36:38.100 --> 01:36:41.069
That was reality
up there, Mr. Vernon.

01:36:41.137 --> 01:36:44.334
And if you can't accept
that for what it is,

01:36:44.406 --> 01:36:48.206
then you can take
your deal and you can
shove it up your ass.

01:36:52.047 --> 01:36:57.075
I found it refreshing
and I respect you for it.

01:37:01.190 --> 01:37:02.589
Thank you.

01:37:03.325 --> 01:37:04.917
I'm sorry. Are we still...

01:37:05.261 --> 01:37:06.285
We'll see.

01:37:07.630 --> 01:37:09.029
This is why
you keep firing me.

01:37:09.098 --> 01:37:10.998
I'll be right back.
Mr. Vernon?

01:37:26.949 --> 01:37:30.146
There's something
I don't think
you ever realized.

01:37:30.519 --> 01:37:32.419
As far as
we were concerned,

01:37:32.488 --> 01:37:34.388
we didn't just
lose our daughter.

01:37:35.057 --> 01:37:36.854
We also lost our son.

01:37:39.195 --> 01:37:40.184
I'm sorry.

01:37:40.462 --> 01:37:41.451
We understand.

01:37:43.265 --> 01:37:46.723
And she would want you
to just get on
with your life.

01:37:47.903 --> 01:37:49.700
And don't be a stranger.

01:37:49.772 --> 01:37:52.639
But next time
make sure you use
the front door.

01:37:52.708 --> 01:37:54.505
I will. I promise.

01:37:55.244 --> 01:37:58.975
And listen.
Thank you, son.
Thank you.

01:37:59.748 --> 01:38:01.238
Look, I should have done this
a long time ago.

